  "title": "Engineer [ Diploma in Electrical | High Voltage | Switchgears ]",
  "description": "<ul><li><p><strong>Position: Assistant Electrical Engineer</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Basic Salary:  $2,400 to $3,000</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Entitled to Yearly Bonus & Performance Bonus</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>5 Work Days Per Week</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Working Location: Joo Koon, Singapore [ West ]</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Transport Pickup Points at Paya Lebar, Serangoon, Bishan, Jurong East, Joon Koon & Woodlands</strong></p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ol><li><p>Diploma of Electrical Engineering or Electronic.</p></li><li><p>Minimum one (1) years’ experience in electrical engineering environment.</p></li><li><p><em><strong>Interest to work long term and build career in Power Engineering Industry [ High Voltage ]</strong></em></p></li></ol><p></p><p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></p><p>Job Description</p><ol><li><p>To attend to site survey/meetings/discussions with client/contractors/sub-contractors on related matters together with the LEW (when required). Providing feasible solutions and coordinate with owners/users, consultants, vendors/contractors on engineering functional requirements and ensure the objectives are achieved.</p></li><li><p>Ability to prepare report and method statement whenever necessary. Perform all electrical works in adherence to EMA regulations and guidelines with the LEW supervision</p></li><li><p>Assisting the PE/LEW to carry out regular site inspections on LT and HT installations to ensure that all maintenance programmes are implemented effectively in strict compliance with instructions and guidelines.</p></li><li><p>Standby and partnering with LEW in attending to emergency call up services at customer installations. Investigate and determine the root cause of the faults and report (where applicable)</p></li><li><p>Able to interpret basic schematics and SLD diagrams. Required to take on a Specialist Equipment role, may be sent to receive specialised training and subsequently providing training to internal staff.</p></li><li><p>Plan and execution of corrective or preventive maintenance programme. Participate in and support Annual Shutdown exercises as and when required. Ensure proper housekeeping of spare parts, equipment and tools.</p></li><li><p>Assist the LEW in Test and commissioning of electrical system. Provide excellent service to meet client expectations. Ensure all works carried out safely and / or in accordance with safety procedures.</p></li></ol><p></p><p>#SCR-carson-cheong</p><p>⭕ Cheong Kar Chun ⭕ Team Manager ⭕ R1980386</p><p>⭕ The Supreme HR Advisory ⭕ 14C7279</p>",
